    "body": "### Contact Details (e.g. Tox ID or email)\n\ntox:5A18C1D8A76616C0D98865D175C777B242F2F3188411D8C87038303C980FFB1172CBC355EBFD\n\n### qTox Version\n\nv1.17.90-55-g3cc1cf195\n\n### Commit Hash\n\n3cc1cf19507251dd37da061d212c3bd758e2633e\n\n### Toxcore Version\n\n0.2.20\n\n### Qt Version\n\n6.4.2\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Start qTox\r\n2. Have a chat where someone sends files (pictures for example).\r\n3. Make the window quite small (on Linux this is how I can reproduce, on macOS it happens a lot more).\r\n4. Scroll up and down (maybe you need to send some messages to fill the chat log with something to scroll around in).\n\n### Observed Behavior\n\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/953af64a-9e9f-4aea-ae79-c12ed56089a5)\r\n\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nThe green box should only be partially shown and stop at the horizontal line.\n\n### Reproducibility\n\nAlways\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Operating System version/distro/name/etc.\n\nDebian GNU/Linux\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n```shell\nNothing special to see in the logs.\n```\n",
